This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump in the Oval Office regarding the case of Vanessa Guillén, a soldier who was killed on a military base. Guillén's family, including her mother and sisters, met with the President to seek justice for her death. The family described the sexual harassment and abuse that Guillén experienced before her murder, and they called for reforms in the military to protect soldiers from such incidents. They also discussed the need for a congressional investigation into the case and the importance of passing a bill to provide soldiers with better protections. President Trump expressed his sympathy and promised to take action, including involving the FBI and DOJ in the investigation. He also offered to help with the funeral expenses and expressed his support for the family's quest for justice.